**etcd Client Library Configuration:**
The etcd client library defines the DialTimeout field in `client/v3/config.go` as a time.Duration field with JSON tag "dial-timeout". This config field controls how long the client waits when establishing connections to etcd servers.

**etcd Client Usage:**
The DialTimeout is actively used throughout the etcd client library:
- In `client/v3/client.go`, DialTimeout is used to set context timeout when dialing gRPC connections using `context.WithTimeout(c.ctx, c.cfg.DialTimeout)`
- In `client/v3/lease.go`, DialTimeout is added to lease client timeout calculations
- In `client/v3/maintenance.go`, DialTimeout is used similarly for maintenance operation timeouts

