The etcd server uses DialTimeout for peer-to-peer raft communication:
- `server/config/config.go` defines the `PeerDialTimeout()` method which calculates peer dial timeout as 1 second plus the election timeout (calculated from ElectionTicks and TickMs)
- `server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go` stores DialTimeout in the Transport struct and uses it when creating stream and pipeline round trippers for peer communication
- `server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/util.go` contains `NewRoundTripper()` and `newStreamRoundTripper()` functions that accept the dialTimeout parameter for creating HTTP transports used in raft message exchange
- `server/etcdserver/server.go` uses `cfg.PeerDialTimeout()` when creating rafthttp.Transport for peer communication and calls `rafthttp.NewRoundTripper()` with the peer dial timeout

