The lower-level transport layer implements the actual timeout enforcement:
- `client/pkg/transport/transport.go` has `NewTransport()` function that accepts dialtimeoutd parameter and creates http.Transport with net.Dialer timeout
- `client/pkg/transport/timeout_transport.go` has `NewTimeoutTransport()` function that wraps the basic transport with read/write timeout support, using the dialtimeoutd for dial timeout configuration

This architecture shows a complete chain from the Kubernetes API server's 20-second DialTimeout through the etcd client library's timeout handling, down to the actual TCP dial timeout enforcement at the net.Dialer level, with additional configurations for peer communication timeouts and proxy timeouts throughout the etcd server subsystems."
